National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Preliminary Report
Location: McDougal, AR
Accident Number: CEN19FA020
Date & Time: 11/02/2018, 1330 CDT
Registration: N5187S
Aircraft: Hughes 369
Injuries: 1 Fatal, 2 Minor
Flight Conducted Under: Part 133: Rotorcraft Ext. Load
On October 2, 2018 about 1330 central daylight time (CDT), a Hughes 369D, N5187S/N454AR, 
was destroyed when it impacted a utility pole and, subsequently, terrain in McDougal, 
Arkansas. The helicopter departed from a grass landing zone with two linemen attached for 
short haul operations in connection with utility line work. The commercial pilot was fatally 
injured and the two lineman sustained minor injuries. Visual meteorological conditions 
prevailed for the external load operation that was conducted under the provisions of 14 
Code of 
Federal Regulations
 Part 133, and no flight plan had been filed.
